## A New Service Experience for Corporate Clients: WeChat-based online support for HSBCnet-related enquiries — **faster responses, smooth escalation, and end-to-end resolution**

## Problem Statement

* **Service transition gap:** The Livechat (online agent support) on HSBCnet was discontinued last year. As a result, HSBCnet clients no longer have a dedicated online channel for agent support, and available enquiry entry points have been reduced.
* **Complex journey, lower efficiency:** For more complex services (e.g., HSBCnet and Bank Confirmation), longer and multi-step processes can lead to higher communication effort and lower efficiency. Non-specialist users may also find it difficult to describe their needs accurately, which can create information gaps.
* **High reliance on manual support:** The current chatbot mainly covers a subset of FAQs, while some newly introduced services in recent years are not yet fully included. When the chatbot cannot resolve an enquiry, corporate clients often need to switch to offline or alternative channels, which takes additional time and effort.

## Solution

* **Core enhancement:** An upgraded **Livechat + Chatbot** capability is now available via **HSBC China Corporate WeChat Official Account / GBA Corporate Service Mini Program**. Clients can start an enquiry in WeChat first; if the chatbot cannot meet the need, they can tap **“Transfer to agent”** to connect to Livechat (online agent support). HSBCnet-related issues can be discussed and handled online, reducing offline follow-ups.
* **Chatbot upgrade in parallel:** The new chatbot is powered by AI, leveraging natural language processing and machine learning to improve automated responses for common enquiries. A new **“similar question + keyword matching”** feature helps improve answer relevance and consistency. Coverage is further expanded (estimated **+30%**), with **700+** FAQs consolidated, and additional content added for HSBCnet, Bank Confirmation, and bank information, spanning common topics across **GPS, GTS, Onboarding**, and more.
* **Dynamic menu to guide enquiries:** The upgraded chatbot introduces a dynamic menu with step-by-step options to help clients quickly identify the right topic and information. Clients can follow the menu instead of drafting detailed messages, enabling more precise issue routing and responses.
* **End-to-end online journey, one-stop closed loop:** Client enters the Official Account/Mini Program → raises an enquiry → chatbot responds automatically (resolving common issues directly). If agent support is required, the client can tap or type **“agent”** to connect to Livechat and communicate with a dedicated service representative to drive resolution through to closure.

## Impact

* **Improved responsiveness:** Faster overall response and handling for corporate enquiries, with fewer back-and-forth clarifications—helping frontline teams focus more capacity on complex cases.
* **Better end-to-end experience:** A dedicated Livechat (online agent support) entry point reduces friction from offline processes and multi-channel switching, making the experience more convenient and seamless.
* **Smarter service capability:** Broader chatbot coverage and more intelligent responses help reduce communication cost, increase self-service resolution for day-to-day enquiries, and improve overall efficiency.

